# Shared layout system (required)

## Required page shell for every HTML page
- Include exactly one `#app-header` mount container.
- Include exactly one `#app-footer` mount container.
- Include `<script src="/js/layout.js"></script>` near the end of `body`.
- Breadcrumbs are optional and must use a dedicated `[data-breadcrumbs]` mount (do not hardcode breadcrumb markup).

## Do not reintroduce legacy duplicated layout markup
- Do not add hardcoded `<header class="site-header">` in page files.
- Do not add hardcoded `<footer class="site-footer">` in page files.
- Do not add duplicated mobile drawer markup (`mobile-nav-drawer`) in page files.
- Do not add inline nav toggle scripts (`navToggle`, `mobileDrawer`, click/Escape handlers) in page files.
- Do not add page-specific sticky/mobile navigation behavior in page files.
- Do not manually set nav active classes or page-level `aria-current` in page files.

## Centralized change policy
- Header/footer structure, sticky behavior, mobile drawer behavior, active-link logic, `aria-current`, and nav accessibility behavior must be changed centrally in `js/layout.js`.
- Shared visual and state styling for global navigation/layout must be changed in `styles.css` (or other shared global styles), not duplicated per page.
- If a page needs a unique local section nav, it must not duplicate the global site header/footer/navigation system.
